                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/182a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Special Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="113" xml:id="d1362fn113">Same to Consul, Durango.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Spanish Ambassador informs Department that despite Villa’s assurances regarding
                    protection of foreign property, Constitutionalist forces under Tomas Urbina have
                    confiscated the Desengaño mine at Guanacevi, Durango, belonging to Rodriguez
                    Brothers, Spanish subjects. Use best efforts to secure restitution of this
                    property.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
